cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.CR

This paper deals with the optimization of resource allocation and routing in SDN-based networks for energy efficiency and quality of service. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves modeling and optimization problems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper addresses the reduction of energy consumption, which could be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper deals with security functions such as IDS and firewall, which could be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
